<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-10-05T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-10-05T04:00:00-05:00" n="341" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d341">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">125.643/56: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-10-05T17:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">October 5,
                                        1928—5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received October 5—11:40
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>748. Your telegram No. 334, October 4, 3 p.m.</p>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>Associated Press report of a deadlock is not correct. Status of
                                the matter is unchanged since Legation’s No. 719, September 20, 6
                                p.m. We are still awaiting word from Wang both as to his efforts to
                                overcome factional opposition to the arrangements offered by him and
                                as to the progress of repairs of consulate.</item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>My recommendation is that we should not seek to force the issue
                                one way or the other but await the outcome of Wang’s efforts to
                                arrange the matter.</item>
                        </list>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>